I think you may have a fundamental misunderstanding about what happens in the communication process on FileTAO.

Communication on FileTAO works as follows:

`client -> validator (api) -> miners -> validator -> client`

As the client you do not have control over which miners store the data, but rather which *validators* running api nodes store your data for you. This is the job and function of the validator abstraction in the first place. It indexes and handles this *for * you so you don't have to.  All you need to keep track of is the `CID` (conten-identifier) hash of your data to retrieve it later 🙃 

I believe what you are aiming to do is point the store function at a particular api node uid (not miner), who is running a registered and staked (>500 tao) validator hotkey. The api node then chunks the file, decides (pseudo-randomly with heuristics to calculate an optimal mutually-exclusive set of) miners to populate the data with, forwards those data to them, and then returns to you the `CID` hash which is your "ticket" to retrieving your data at any point in the future.
